Phase 3 hotfix (v0.4.1): JE Relation row self-heal — L-021

End-to-end testing on Brick Builder HQ staging surfaced a critical
gap in the link-resolution logic. The user's recent mosaic CCT
saves were logging skipped_no_target because:

1. JetEngine's "Has Single Page" feature creates the linked post
   on CCT save and stores its ID in cct_single_post_id.
2. JetEngine does NOT auto-write a row to {prefix}jet_rel_{id}.
   That only happens when the editor explicitly attaches via the
   picker UI.

So mosaics 2/3/4 had real linked products (via cct_single_post_id)
but no relation rows — and the v0.4.0 flattener only checked the
relation table, gave up, and never even reached the condition check.

This release self-heals the gap.

Engine changes:
- JEDB_Flattener::resolve_target_id() now returns a tuple
  [target_id, resolution_method, auto_attached] and follows a
  3-step resolution chain when link_via.type = 'je_relation':
    (1) JE Relation row lookup — fast path, when present.
    (2) Fallback to cct_single_post_id when no relation row exists,
        link_via.fallback_to_single_page is on (default true), and
        the linked post's type matches the relation's other endpoint.
    (3) Auto-attach the missing relation row via the existing
        idempotent JEDB_Relation_Attacher::attach() when
        link_via.auto_attach_relation is on (default true). After
        the first sync, JE Smart Filters / Listing Grids / Query
        Builder traversals work natively, and subsequent syncs use
        the fast path.
- New private verify_single_post_matches_relation() rejects
  type-mismatched candidates so we won't bridge, e.g., a story_bricks
  post into a mosaics_data → product relation.
- apply_bridge() destructures the tuple and threads resolution +
  auto_attached metadata into every sync log row's context_json.
  No-target rows also gain has_single_page so the user can see at
  a glance why the resolver gave up.

Config schema:
- Two new flags in link_via, both default true:
    fallback_to_single_page
    auto_attach_relation
- merge_with_defaults() now deep-merges the link_via subtree so
  bridges saved before 0.4.1 get the new keys filled in on read
  (no migration needed).

Admin UI:
- New "Self-heal options" fieldset in the Flatten edit form with
  two checkboxes + explanatory help text. JS wires them into the
  config_json on submit and on change.

Documentation:
- LESSONS-LEARNED L-021 — full root-cause analysis with the user's
  actual SQL evidence + corrects the conflated language in earlier
  L-016 / D-17.
- BUILD-PLAN section 4.5 — adds "Self-heal: auto-attach when JE
  Relation row is missing" subsection with a flag table.
- D-13 / D-17 refined to distinguish relation DEFINITIONS (manual
  / preset-only) from relation ROWS (self-heal automatic).
- CHANGELOG full 0.4.1 entry.
- README + readme.txt + workspace docs version-bumped.

No schema migration required. Existing 0.4.0 bridges work as-is
with self-heal turned ON by default. Strict explicit-attach
behavior is available by unchecking the two flags per bridge.
